chmark and an automatic performance model generator for architecture-level performance models based on the Palladio Component Model. To compare the techniques we conduct two experiments with different levels of granularity on a standalone system, followed by one experiment using a distributed SPECjEnterprise2010 deployment combining both extraction classes for generating a full-stack performance model.},\n}\n\n','\n\nFelix Willnecker, Markus Dlugi, Andreas Brunnert, Simon Spinner, Samuel Kounev,\nand Helmut Krcmar.\nComparing the Accuracy of Resource Demand Measurement and Estimation\nTechniques.\nIn <em>Computer Performance Engineering - Proceedings of the 12th\nEuropean Workshop (EPEW 2015)</em>, Marta Beltr&aacute;n, William Knottenbelt, and\nJeremy Bradley, editors, Madrid, Spain, August 2015, volume 9272 of <em>\nLecture Notes in Computer Science</em>, pages 115-129. Springer.\nAugust 2015.\n[&nbsp;<a class=\"abstract-a\" onclick=\"showAbstract(\'bib-of-WiDlBrSpKoKr2015-EPEW-LibredePMWT\')\">bib</a>&nbsp;| <a href=\"http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-23267-6_8\" target=\"blank\">DOI</a>&nbsp;| <a href=\"http://se2.informatik.uni-wuerzburg.de/pa/publications/download/paper/887.pdf\" target=\"blank\">.pdf</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a class=\"abstract-a\" onclick=\"showAbstract(\'WiDlBrSpKoKr2015-EPEW-LibredePMWT\')\">Abstract</a>&nbsp; ] <div id=\"bib-of-WiDlBrSpKoKr2015-EPEW-LibredePMWT\" class=\"inline-bib\" style=\"display:none;\"><pre>\n@inproceedings{WiDlBrSpKoKr2015-EPEW-LibredePMWT,\nauthor = {Felix Willnecker and Markus Dlugi and Andreas Brunnert and Simon Spinner and Samuel Kounev and Helmut Krcmar},\ntitle = {{Comparing the Accuracy of Resource Demand Measurement and Estimation Techniques}},\nbooktitle = {Computer Performance Engineering - Proceedings of the 12th European Workshop (EPEW 2015)},\nlocation = {Madrid, Spain},\nseries = {Lecture Notes in Computer Science},\nvolume = {9272},\npages = {115-129},\neditor = {Beltr\\\'{a}n, Marta and Knottenbelt, William